                            <p class="mb-0">2. What do you mean by process synchronization? </p>
                            <p id="ans2" class="interview_ans mb-0"><i class="fa fa-arrow-right text-primary me-2"></i>Process synchronization is basically a way to coordinate processes that use shared resources or data. It is very much essential to ensure synchronized execution of cooperating processes so that will maintain data consistency. Its main purpose is to share resources without any interference using mutual exclusion. There are two types of process synchronization :
                             <br>1. Independent Process
                             <br>2. Cooperative Process</p>
